[ae] case called 1:41 PM Defendant Nicholas W. Zache in court. Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint appears for the State of Wisconsin. 
The Court reviews case history and inquires about Defendants status of counsel. Defendant provides PFAC and other paperwork for the Courts review. Defendants legal guardian and group home worker appeared. 
The Court reviews the Defendants PFAC and finds that Defendant eligible for Court Appointed Attorney. The Court appoints an attorney for the defendant with no repayment plan 
The Court also has reason to doubt the Defendants competency and will hold issue open until an attorney can appear with the Defendant

The Court orders the PFAC to remain open for public view. The Court orders the guardianship paperwork submitted to be sealed and only viewable by Defendant, Defendants Attorney, Guardian and State's Attorney.
